HEADWORD: Reticular
<hw>Re*tic"u*lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧ticulaire</ets>. See <er>Reticule</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having the form of a net, or of network; formed with interstices;
